<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The price of USD v JPY has moved above the 156.73 level and that brings the pair back into the view of the BOJ. After two interventions this year, traders have a short memory and longs would be risky.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Data begins on Friday at 7:30am HKT for the Japanese economy with CPI consumer inflation figures. Markets will be looking for any deviation on last month’s 2.6% figure, which was 2.2% in the expected food and energy reading. Anything higher could speed up the Bank of Japan’s plan for a rate increase.</span></p>
